.TH "omap3xxx_prm_dpll3_reset" 9 "omap3xxx_prm_dpll3_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap3xxx_prm_dpll3_reset \- use DPLL3 reset to reboot the OMAP SoC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" omap3xxx_prm_dpll3_reset
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Set the DPLL3 reset bit, which should reboot the SoC.  This is the
recommended way to restart the SoC, considering Errata i520.  No
return value.
